    "303107": {
        "Desc": "Talk to everyone",
        "Talk": [
            [
                {
                    "N": "Wanderer",
                    "T": "You're a god... Do you think I'm evil?"
                },
                {
                    "N": "Nahida",
                    "T": "If you accept that he is you, just as you are you, then yes â€” you are evil."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Wanderer",
                    "T": "In your eyes, are there any differences between humans and puppets?"
                },
                {
                    "N": "Nahida",
                    "T": "Do you think there are any differences between your present self and your previous and future incarnations? If not, then what are the differences between humans and puppets?"
                },
                {
                    "N": "Nahida",
                    "T": "Whoever has tasted the joys and sorrows of life in the human realm is human. Whoever has loved and lost, cried with grief, howled with rage at the tragedy of death that eclipses the miracle of life... they are human, too."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Wanderer",
                    "T": "..."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Wanderer",
                    "T": "I've seen enough of my past. If possible, I'd like to reclaim the sins that are mine to bear."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Wanderer",
                    "T": "No matter the consequences, I won't run from blame or punishment. Whatever I am due, let it come to pass."
                },
                {
                    "N": "_0",
                    "T": "Are you saying..."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Wanderer",
                    "T": "Can you return my memories to me?"
                },
                {
                    "N": "_1005",
                    "T": "Huh? But won't that mean you'll lose your current identity?"
                },
                {
                    "N": "Wanderer",
                    "T": "I've always believed that human lives follow a set of rules, with each person being a collection of past experiences."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Wanderer",
                    "T": "As a puppet living in the human world, my life is subject to the same rules."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Nahida",
                    "T": "Regaining your memories means reverting completely to your previous incarnation. All the emotions that you discarded will return to you."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Nahida",
                    "T": "Are you sure you want to do this?"
                },
                {
                    "N": "Wanderer",
                    "T": "I've lived with a void in my chest my whole life. My creator didn't need me, and ever since I awoke, I've just drifted from one place to the next."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Wanderer",
                    "T": "But then I met you, and I finally realized that reclaiming my missing sins might be my one opportunity to become my true self."
                },
                {
                    "N": "_0",
                    "T": "(...Is this the true meaning of Greater Lord Rukkhadevata's words? A person can't erase themselves, and even though the original Balladeer has gone, this person will live on in his place...)"
                },
                {
                    "N": "_0",
                    "T": "(Are a person's sins an inescapable part of their destiny too?)"
                },
                {
                    "N": "Wanderer",
                    "T": "I've always felt I have an innate tendency to yearn for something more, in a way that goes deeper than for most people... But for all my soul-searching as a shugenja, I've never fully understood it. Looking at it now, it seems that I brought this curse upon myself."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Wanderer",
                    "T": "So I beg you... grant me this opportunity to gain a purpose. To change my destiny and end my wandering."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Nahida",
                    "T": "Very well."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Nahida",
                    "T": "Since your mind is made up, I will return to you that which is yours."
                }
            ]
        ]
    },
